    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Game pieces used in the game of the same name that originated in Belgium The piece comprises a sculpted wooden bird, often decorated, with a metal pin in the beak, that is suspended from the ceiling or a cross beam by rope. The bird is aimed at a target by players, not unlike a game of darts.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
